The paper deals with a machine learning problem of topic modeling, which involves clustering and unsupervised learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which are also related to natural language processing. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for estimating the parameters of the latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA) model, which is a popular topic modeling technique in the field of machine learning and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper emphasizes the scalability of the proposed algorithm, which is important for large-scale data analysis, and thus cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category.
